The President's statement on South Sudan highlights the country's progress in building a peaceful and prosperous future. However, recent violence threatens to undo this progress. The President calls on South Sudan's leaders to end the violence, resolve tensions peacefully, and commit to dialogue. He emphasizes the need for compromise and reconciliation, urging leaders to show courage and reaffirm their commitment to peace and unity. The United States will continue to support the South Sudanese people in their pursuit of security and prosperity.